Multi-Cloud Architecture Demo (AWS + GCP)

 Project Overview
This project demonstrates a **multi-cloud architecture** where the frontend and backend are deployed independently and communicate using REST APIs.  
The frontend simulates deployment on **Google Cloud**, while the backend API simulates deployment on **AWS**.

---

 Objective
To showcase:
- Cross-cloud communication
- REST API interaction
- Backend–frontend decoupling
- Multi-cloud interoperability

---

 Architecture Overview

- **Frontend**
  - HTML + JavaScript
  - Served using Python HTTP server
  - Simulates Google Cloud hosting

- **Backend**
  - Python Flask REST API
  - Flask-CORS enabled
  - Simulates AWS backend service

- **Communication**
  - REST APIs (HTTP POST/GET)
  - JSON data exchange

---

 Technologies Used

- Python 3.8
- Flask
- Flask-CORS
- HTML
- JavaScript
- VS Code

---

